%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228660%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20woman%20drinking%20a%20protein%20shake%20in%20the%20gym%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695ecea7832e0ef1ead75ea2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225773%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWomen%20are%20a%20major%20audience%20for%20protein%20products%20from%20shakes%20to%20snacks%2C%20fueled%20in%20part%20by%20the%20growing%20popularity%20of%20strength%20training.%3Cp%3EATHVisions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20boom%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-loss-glp-1-drugs-ozempic-wegovy-mounjaro-effects-future-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGLP-1%20drugs%20for%20weight%20loss%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20brought%20protein%20to%20the%20forefront%2C%20as%20Americans%20have%20pushed%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20muscle%20mass%20while%20losing%20fat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtein%20is%20also%20a%20crucial%20nutrient%20for%20longevity.%20As%20we%20get%20older%2C%20our%20muscle%20mass%20tends%20to%20naturally%20decline%2C%20which%2C%20if%20we're%20not%20careful%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20frailty%20and%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20injury%20and%20illness.%20Eating%20enough%20protein%20as%20we%20age%20helps%20maintain%20muscle%20for%20more%20resilience%20and%20strength%20at%20age%2060%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20dietary%20guidelines%20focused%20on%20the%20bare%20minimum%20of%20protein%20you'd%20need%20to%20avoid%20malnutrition%2C%20which%20is%20around%200.36%20grams%20per%20pound%20of%20body%20weight%20(about%2054%20grams%20per%20day%20for%20a%20150-pound%20person).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20avoiding%20starvation%20is%20rarely%20the%20only%20goal%20of%20eating.%20Nutrition%20and%20exercise%20science%20suggest%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-protein-maximize-muscle-gains-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoptimal%20amount%20of%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20building%20muscle%20is%20about%20twice%20that%20amount%2C%20about%200.7%20grams%20per%20pound%20daily%20(105%20grams%20for%20a%20150-pound%20person).%20In%20a%20day%2C%20that%20translates%20to%20about%2030%20to%2035%20grams%20per%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226bebc98f-a5fc-4c7b-908f-ce22dcd5d3ab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20protein%20overrated%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20some%20top%20TikTokers%20log%20themselves%20eating%20more%20than%20100%20grams%20of%20protein%20at%20a%20single%20meal%2C%20and%20300%20or%20more%20grams%20in%20a%20day.%20Great%2C%20if%20you're%20the%20Rock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20rest%20of%20us%2C%20there's%20no%20reason%20to%20spend%20that%20extra%20time%2C%20money%2C%20and%20energy%20on%20all%20that%20protein%2C%20said%20Dr.%20Federica%20Amati%2C%20medical%20scientist%20and%20head%20nutritionist%20at%20the%20nutrition%20app%20ZOE.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDefinitely%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20overrated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20interest%20in%20protein%20isn't%20going%20anywhere%20because%20it's%20been%20ingrained%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20US%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtein%20has%20been%20a%20mainstay%20of%20American%20nutrition%20for%20well%20over%20four%20decades%3A%20from%20the%20Atkins%20era%20in%20the%2070s%2C%20peaking%20in%20the%20early%20aughts%2C%20to%20current%20keto%2C%20low-carb%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarnivore-diet-claims-eating-only-meat-helps-fitness-weight-loss-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecarnivore%20diets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Along%20the%20way%2C%20food%20fads%20alternatively%20demonized%20dietary%20fats%20and%20carbs.%20For%20any%20health-conscious%20person%2C%20what%20else%20was%20left%20to%20eat%20but%20more%20and%20more%20protein%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20according%20to%20Amati%20and%20others%2C%20is%20that%20protein%20is%20hogging%20the%20spotlight%20from%20other%20key%20nutrients%20that%20play%20a%20major%20role%20in%20our%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20close-up%20of%20thick%20steaks%20on%20a%20cutting%20board%20with%20a%20few%20asparagus%20spears%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695ed0d704eda4732f2eac9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOverloading%20protein%20can%20leave%20less%20room%20for%20veggies%20and%20other%20nutrient-dense%20foods.%3Cp%3EJuefrateam%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20just%20focus%20on%20telling%20people%20you%20need%20to%20eat%20one%20gram%20of%20protein%20for%20a%20kilogram%20of%20body%20weight%2C%20then%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20else%20is%20going%20on%20the%20plate%2C%26quot%3B%20Amati%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiber%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20gut%20health%2C%20metabolism%2C%20and%20longevity.%20And%20you're%20far%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-spector-increase-fiber-plant-based-protein-sources-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emissing%20out%20on%20fiber%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20protein%2C%20Amati%20said.%20Incidentally%2C%20the%20latest%20dietary%20guidelines%20put%20key%20sources%20of%20fiber%2C%20like%20beans%20and%20whole%20grains%2C%20near%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20pyramid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20for%20athletes%2C%20who%20need%20extra%20protein%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20strain%20of%20exercise%2C%20can%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-that-look-healthy-heart-disease-failure-stroke-inflammation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etoo%20much%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cardiologist%20Dr.%20Dmitry%20Yaranov%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Bodybuilders%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20look%20like%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20health%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bend%20up%20with%20weak%20hearts%20and%20blocked%20arteries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22639966c4-aa26-42ef-9eb3-e68fd415b288%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20get%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20protein%20for%20your%20goals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20dietary%20guidelines%20recommend%20between%200.6%20and%200.9%20grams%20of%20protein%20per%20pound%20of%20body%20weight%20daily%2C%20between%2090%20and%20135%20grams%20for%20a%20150-pound%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Amati%20said%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20track%20your%20grams%20of%20protein%20at%20all.%20If%20you%20simply%20must%20count%20your%20protein%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20she%20recommends%20calculating%20a%20percentage%20instead%20of%20the%20number%20of%20grams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20eating%20around%202000%20calories%20a%20day%2C%20100%20grams%20of%20protein%20would%20translate%20to%20about%2020%25%20of%20your%20diet%2C%20leaving%20the%20other%2080%25%20of%20your%20diet%20for%20more%20crucial%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20percentage%20helps%20us%20do%20is%20focus%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20a%20varied%20diet%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtein%20sources%20also%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeat%20makes%20up%20a%20large%20part%20of%20Kennedy's%20new%20vision%20of%20healthy%20eating%20in%20America%20(including%20our%20right%20to%20fries%20soaked%20in%20cattle%20fat)%2C%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-eat-more-butter-full-fat-milk-dietary-guidelines-dairy-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecomeback%20movement%20for%20dairy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20butter%2C%20and%20other%20animal-based%20foods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20red%20and%20processed%20meats%20(including%20trendy%20jerky%20snacks%20and%20deli%20meats)%20have%20consistently%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20heart%20disease%20and%20some%20cancers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmati%20said%20your%20best%20bet%